# Architecture

```
src/
  main.tsx, App.tsx          # Entry + routing
  routes/                    # Page components (thin — wire data to UI)
  components/                # UI (layout/, examples/, capstones/)
  engine/                    # Business logic (grading, queues, Pyodide, traces)
  store/                     # Zustand stores (progress persistence)
  content/                   # Data layer
    schema.ts                # Zod schemas (source of truth for shapes)
    registry.ts              # Aggregates lessons, exams, capstones
    lessons/                 # One file per lesson
    capstones/               # Capstone projects + walkthrough helpers
    examSets/                # Timed exam content
  styles/                    # Global CSS
tests/                       # Vitest unit tests (mirror engine/store)
e2e/                         # Playwright smoke tests
scripts/                     # validate-content, migrations, generators
```

## Layer rules

1. **content/** — declarative data only; no React imports.
2. **engine/** — pure functions and async runtimes; no React imports.
3. **store/** — may import engine + content/registry; no component imports.
4. **components/** — may import engine, store, content; keep pages in routes/.
5. **routes/** — compose components; minimal logic.

## Adding features

- New example type → extend `content/schema.ts`, `engine/grader.ts`, and `ExampleCard.tsx`.
- New route → add to `App.tsx` and `HudHeader.viewportTitle()`.
- Progress fields → bump `schemaVersion` in `store/progress.ts` with migration in `persist` middleware.
